CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper August 3, 1957, pg. B4, reads: "Tops in Track - The Ammon Center track and field team, which has many trophies and other laurels, continued its winning ways last week in a track and field meet, sponsored by Ammon, at the Homestead High School Athletic Field Friday night. Ammon stars, as a team, and coached by Charles Betts, won top honors in competition with eight other teams. Those members are, standing, left to right: Dorlin Taylor, William Munroe, Theodore Woods, Harold Martin, Larry Goodman, Raymond Brown and Walter Harris, manager. Kneeling: Sam Maxwell, Francis Bressiett, Otis Edwards, Robert Williams, William Belt and Robert Penn. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Ammon Center track team standing from left: Dorlin Taylor, William Munroe, Theodore Woods, Harold Martin, Larry Goodman, Raymond Brown, Walter Harris: kneeling: Sam Maxwell, Francis Bressiett, Otis Edwards, Robert Williams, William Belt and Robert Penn posed on Homestead High School field
